	<Title>
		Buying new workout shoes? Get the right fit
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;If you&apos;re shopping for new athletic shoes, be sure to try on both shoes and wiggle your toes. If you don&apos;t have at least a half an inch (1.3 centimeters) between your longest toe and the end of the shoe, go up a size. If you can detect the outline of your toes in the top or on the side of the shoe, try a larger size or wider shoe. Finally, be sure the shoe is wide enough. The side-to-side fit of the shoe should be snug, not tight.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
